      <Subject xmlns="urn:xmlns:nl:pop-project:vocab:Subjects#">D50000</Subject>
      <Abstract xml:lang="en">The proposed research aims to integrate cognitive, affective and motivational theories of religious beliefs. A cognitive approach, stating that religious beliefs originate from the mnemonic advantages of counterintuitive concepts, is used as an underlying model in which additional approaches to religion are integrated. The emotion arousing properties of religious beliefs are tested by registering Skin Conductance Responses when people are exposed to counterintuitive concepts. Counterintuitive concepts are also related to the human motivation to manage existential anxieties, and hence the effects of death-related thoughts on the appraisal of counterintuitive concepts are assessed.</Abstract>
